# OnKartHit is the first .text fn = coloring-driver FN#0. Only its class-4 (GPR)
# callee-saved partition (reg r25..r31) is reproduced here; the volatile webs and
# the FPR (class-3) step are elided. Variable<->reg identity is from objdiff rows.
#
# BASELINE (96.38% C body, decl order rm-first):
#   key=94 deg=14 reg=r31 flags=0x02 adjN=102   <- rm   (local; target wants r29)
#   key=52 deg=16 reg=r30 flags=0x02 adjN=77    <- bus  (local; target wants r25)
#   key=51 deg=14 reg=r29 flags=0x42 adjN=42    <- coalesced bool/reuse web
#   key=50 deg=12 reg=r29 flags=0x42 adjN=40    <- coalesced
#   key=49 deg=12 reg=r30 flags=0x42 adjN=46    <- coalesced
#   key=47 deg=12 reg=r28 flags=0x42 adjN=33    <- coalesced
#   key=33 deg=16 reg=r27 flags=0x02 adjN=137   <- victim (PARAM; target wants r31)
#   key=32 deg=16 reg=r26 flags=0x02 adjN=135   <- self   (PARAM; target wants r30)
#   key=46 deg=12 reg=r25 flags=0x42 adjN=26    <- coalesced (popped last, #151)
#
# EXPERIMENT V1 (hoist rm to the first statement): rm key 94 -> 65, but home reg
#   UNCHANGED (still r31). self/victim UNCHANGED at key 32/33 -> r26/r27.
#   -> source def-order moves a web's KEY but NOT its home; params stay pinned.
# EXPERIMENT E2b (KartItemHit *self = selfP; born first as a local copy):
#   BYTE-IDENTICAL 96.38%. self still key=32 r26, victim still key=33 r27. The
#   local copy coalesced back into the incoming-param web (param-merge); the param
#   web persists at the lowest callee key. -> param home NOT liftable from source.
#
# PINNING MECHANISM (observed): the two param webs (self,victim) have the MAXIMUM
# interference (adjN 135/137 -- live across the whole fn, interfere with every
# other web) and high degree (16). The Briggs simplify can only push them onto the
# select stack LAST (they cannot be simplified until all neighbours are removed),
# so they are colored LAST and take the LOWEST callee regs (r26/r27). TARGET wants
# them at the TOP (r30/r31), i.e. the params must OUTRANK the locals -- which only
# happens when the params do NOT dominate the interference graph. That ranking is
# fixed by the (already-matched) whole-fn usage of self/victim, not by decl/def
# order. VERDICT: register-identity park is PINNED by param-interference, NOT a
# source-movable web-birth-order lever. See HANDOFF.md / phase2f research note.

